132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1231
H.P. 806 House of Representatives, March 25, 2025
An Act Requiring Ferries to Dock Overnight on Certain Islands for
Emergency Purposes
Reference to the Committee on Transportation suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative FAULKINGHAM of Winter Harbor.
Cosponsored by Senator BEEBE-CENTER of Knox and
Representatives: ANKELES of Brunswick, BISHOP of Bucksport, MASON of Lisbon,
PARRY of Arundel, RAY of Lincolnville, Senator: GROHOSKI of Hancock.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 23 MRSA §4408 is enacted to read:
3 §4408. Ferries for emergency use
4 To support the use of ferries for emergency medical, fire and law enforcement needs,
5 including mass evacuation, the Department of Transportation shall require the Maine State
6 Ferry Service to nightly dock a ferry vessel that carries vehicles overnight in the towns of
7 Swan's Island, Vinalhaven, North Haven and Islesboro.
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill directs the Department of Transportation to require the Maine State Ferry
1100 Service to nightly dock a ferry vessel that carries vehicles overnight in the towns of Swan's
1111 Island, Vinalhaven, North Haven and Islesboro for emergency medical, fire and law
1122 enforcement needs.
